# Code-as eval

Blind agent evaluations — measure whether `skill/` + `tools/` + CLI give enough
context to complete tasks without monorepo hand-holding.

## Run

```bash
# From repo root:
oota eval list
oota eval run remotion-science-blind
oota eval score remotion-science-blind

# Reset a scenario seed session:
oota eval reset remotion-science-blind
```

## Scenarios

| Id | Task | Blind prompt only |
|----|------|-------------------|
| `remotion-science-blind` | Science video + voice + MP4 | [[eval/scenarios/remotion-science-blind/prompt]] |
| `hardware-smoke` | Hardware + model list | [[eval/scenarios/hardware-smoke/prompt]] |

## Browser viewer

Open the **component surface** in the browser — not the session admin CLI:

```bash
oota serve   # serve this subtree's own nexus :4010 (once)
oota open eval-remotion-science
```

The single universal shell [[components/artifact]] renders every medium.
Agent invokes the URL; user sees preview + `player.work` forms only.

Session admin (routing, evals): `oota admin`

## Isolation model

Each scenario seeds `cli/sessions/eval-<id>/` from `scenarios/<id>/seed/`.
The subagent receives **only** the prompt file text plus instruction to read
`projects/out-of-thin-air/skill/SKILL.md`. Score with `tools/score.sh` against
`rubric.work` checkpoints.

## Metrics

- `checkpoints_passed / checkpoints_total`
- `artifact_exists` per rubric row
- Optional: agent step count (manual or transcript)
